Name: radiobs
Version: 1.0.0
Summary: A set of tools for fitting N-gaussian function to an optical spectrum
Home-page: https://github.com/Fil8/radiobs
Author: Filippo Marcello Maccagni
Author-email: filippo.maccagni@gmail.com
License: GNU GPL 3
Description: ## Radiobs
        
        tools for radioastronomy data analysis
        
        ### Installation
        
        Add `<path to gufo>` to `PYTHONPATH`
          
          - in your `.cshrc`
          `setenv PYTHONPATH <path_to_radiobs>:${PYTHONPATH}`
          - in your `.bashrc`
          `export PYTHONPATH=<path_to_gufo>:$PYTHONPATH`
          
        ### Usage
         In `python` environment type `import gufo` and `from scavengers import gPlay`

         
         find which classes are available.
         
         `gufo.__dict__.keys()`
         
         We choose to read the parameter file and run the fitter
         
          `gPar = gufo.gufo(args.cfgFile)`

          `gp = gPlay.gplay()`

          `gp.gFit(gPar.cfg_par)`
         
        
